<HEADLINE>
These people were not &quot;risking their lives for Harry&quot;, they were risking their lives to defeat Voldemort - an annoyance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> &quot;VBM&quot; &lt;v.mcalis...@nospam.ejgd.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-07-25T19:28:00 </POSTDATE>
Throughout this last book (and in earlier books), we have a lot of angst by
Harry because there are people risking their lives &quot;for him&quot;, as if it is
just out of love for him, or a sacrifice for him *as a person*.  This is
just bunk in most cases.  People were willing to risk their lives to PROTECT
Harry because he was their best weapon against Voldemort.  It was *in their
interest* to protect Harry, or at least in the interest of a cause they
believed in.   Harry is constantly in angst about these people &quot;dying for
him&quot; or &quot;risking their lives for him&quot;, when really he is just a tool, a
weapon, the way they would risk their lives to protect a magical item that
was the only thing that could defeat Voldemort.

Kind of annoying, really.
</POST>
