Ironically, the one person who was actually risking his life
specifically to keep Harry alive was Snape!

Granted, it was because he was Lily's son, but Snape was still focused
completely on Harry's safety.  When he learned late that Dumbledore
was using Harry as a disposable weapon against Voldemort, Snape was
outraged:

“I have spied for you and lied for you, put myself in mortal
danger for you.  Everything was supposed to be to keep Lily Potter’s
son safe. Now you tell me you have been raising him like a pig for
slaughter—”

How's THAT for a turn of events?   ;)
